The paper proposes a model for action recognition in videos using visual attention. This involves analyzing and selectively focusing on parts of the video frames that are relevant for the task at hand. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the model uses multi-layered Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) with Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) units, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning applications. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the model on several datasets commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
